17 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
18 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
19 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
20 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
21 the following proposed amendment to the Constitution of the State of
22 Oklahoma by adding a new Section 49 to Article IX thereof, to read
23 as follows:
24 A. For purposes of this section:
Req. No. 10989 Page 1

1 1. "Cost" means the total projected expenses of planning,
2 constructing, and operating the project, as submitted by the entity
3 seeking to exercise eminent domain;
4 2. "Exclusively" or "primarily" means that more than fifty
5 percent (50%) of the electricity transmitted by the project is
6 generated by wind or solar energy;
7 3. "Financial assistance" means any direct or indirect funding,
8 subsidy, grant, loan, tax credit, or other monetary benefit provided
9 by the United States government, including through agencies,
10 programs, or revolving funds, for the purpose of planning,
11 designing, constructing, or operating the project;
12 4. "Project" means the specific infrastructure, including
13 turbines, transmission lines, and related facilities, proposed for
14 construction, development, or operation; and
15 5. "Tax incentives" means any credit, deduction, exemption, or
16 deferral provided under federal law to encourage the development,
17 operation, or expansion of wind or solar energy projects.
18 B. No person, firm, or corporation organized under the laws of
19 this state, or authorized to do business in this state, to furnish
20 light, heat, or power by electricity or gas, nor any other person,
21 association, or firm engaged in furnishing light, heat, or power by
22 electricity or gas, shall have or exercise the right of eminent
23 domain for:
24
Req. No. 10989 Page 2

1 1. The siting or construction of wind turbines on private
2 property; or
3 2. The siting, building, or construction of transmission lines
4 associated with projects that meet either of the following
5 conditions:
6 a. the project receives financial assistance from the
7 United States government amounting to or exceeding
8 three percent (3%) of the project's total cost, and
9 the transmission lines are used to transmit
10 electricity generated by wind or solar energy, or
11 b. the transmission lines are used exclusively or
12 primarily for transmitting electricity generated by
13 wind or solar energy projects benefiting from tax
14 incentives provided by the United States government.
15 C. Nothing in this section shall:
16 1. Prohibit the voluntary negotiation and acquisition of land
17 by private agreement for wind energy or transmission projects;
18 2. Affect eminent domain authority as applied to projects that
19 do not meet the conditions specified in subsection B of this
20 section; or
21 3. Prohibit energy projects that are not dependent on financial
22 assistance or tax incentives provided by the United States
23 government.
